This paper is about hyperparameter tuning for machine learning models, which is a common problem in the field of machine learning. The paper proposes a novel algorithm for hyperparameter tuning in a massively parallel setting, which is relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), distributed computing (cs.DC), and neural networks (cs.NE). Among these sub-categories, cs.LG is the most likely as it specifically deals with the design and analysis of machine learning algorithms.
